The 63rd annual Grammy Awards has come and gone but this year’s edition is special for Nigerians as two of our Superstars emerged winners. Wizkid and Burna Boy made the list of winners of the prestigious entertainment awards. Trevor Noah, South African US-based comedian, hosted the show from the Los Angeles Convention Center. It was originally scheduled to take place in January but was postponed due to COVID-19 concerns. Here’s the full list of winners: Record of the Year
WINNER: “Everything I Wanted,” Billie Eilish Album of the Year
WINNER: Folklore, Taylor Swift Song of the Year
WINNER: “I Can’t Breathe,” Dernst Emile II, H.E.R. & Tiara Thomas (H.E.R.) Best New Artist
WINNER: Megan Thee Stallion Best Pop Vocal Album
WINNER: Future Nostalgia, Dua Lipa Best R&B Performance
WINNER: “Black Parade,” Beyoncé Best Rap Song
WINNER: “Savage,” Beyoncé, Shawn Carter, Brittany Hazzard, Derrick Milano, Terius Nash, Megan Pete, Bobby Session Jr., Jordan Kyle Lanier Thorpe & Anthony White (Megan Thee Stallion feat. Beyoncé) Best Pop Solo Performance
WINNER: “Watermelon Sugar,” Harry Styles Best Melodic Rap Performance
WINNER: “Lockdown,” Anderson Paak Best Latin Pop or Urban Album
WINNER: YHLQMDLG, Bad Bunny Best Country Album
WINNER: “Crowded Table,” Brandi Carlile, Natalie Hemby & Lori McKenna (The Highwomen) Best Country Duo/Group Performance
WINNER: “10,000 Hours,” Dan + Shay & Justin Bieber Best Rock Album
WINNER: The New Abnormal, The Strokes Best Rock Song
WINNER: “Stay High, Brittany Howard (Brittany Howard) Best Rock Performance
WINNER: “Shameika,” Fiona Apple Best Rap Album
WINNER: King’s Disease, Nas Best Rap Performance
WINNER: “Savage,” Megan Thee Stallion feat. Beyoncé Best Pop Duo/Group Performance
